casebody.data:
PEOPLE State of Illinois, Respondent,
v.
Dontrez WILLIAMS, Petitioner. No. 124390 Supreme Court of Illinois. March 20, 2019

Petition for Leave to Appeal Denied.

In the exercise of this Court's supervisory authority, the Appellate Court, Fourth District, is directed to vacate its judgment in People v. Williams, case No. 4-18-0258 (11/20/18). The appellate court is directed to address defendant's alternative argument that even if the arresting officer had probable cause to detain defendant, the continued detention was unreasonable after two negative show-ups, and determine if a different result is warranted.
